metadata.name: Valley Of The Kings
metadata.description: This photo depicts 2 Egyptian men sitting in front the Philae Temple of Aswan, which was the last temple built to honor the Ancient Egyptian goddess of love Isis. The Philae temple was built around 690 A.D and is considered the last of the ancient temples constructed in the classical Egyptian style. Lion statues stands at the entrance of the temple's pylon with carvings on the wall depicting the Goddess Isis and her son, the God of Kingship, Horus.
